<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Kaylum on 10-22-2001 01:15 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Originally posted by rstimpy:
[B]Beware of scammers, u cant trade a pvp title[/QUOTE]

if they arent scamming, theres 2 things they may be refering to when they auction this "selling pvp title"

1)all you have to do is log in a character of the opposite alignment and allow the other person to kill you over, and over and over until they get a title. they are selling the time it takes to run the character back to the pvp area (ive seen this done in the arena in omni ent)

2) there are "pinky"s in the game. they are a bonus reward for killing someone and having them lose a ton of xp. they can also come from any named npc on extremely rare occasions. look up pinky in the item database to see the description. they can be right clicked to produce a "doh!" over your head. i have 2 of them, and though they are only a novelty item, they have some value due to rarity and they are not no drop.

ps. if you want to know how to sell/trade a no drop, pay me 5mil creds send msg to: Queva
</TEXTAREA>
